[1] China: National Health Commission 24 Apr 2020; 82 816 total cases, 4632 deaths
Date: Fri 24 Apr 2020
Source: China National Health Commission [in Chinese, machine trans., edited]
http://www.nhc.gov.cn/xcs/yqtb/202004/8ca7171cf72b4920a9b37ff5d47fd607.shtml


From 0 to 24:00 on [24 Apr 2020], 31 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps reported 12 newly confirmed cases, of which 11 were imported and 1 was a local case (1 case in Heilongjiang); there were no new deaths reported; 3 new suspected cases, 2 of which were imported from abroad, and 1 was a local suspected case (1 case in Beijing).

On the same day, 89 newly recovered cases were discharged, 566 close contacts were released from medical observation, and the condition of 8 severe cases was downgraded from serious.

There are 720 confirmed imported cases (including 25 severe cases) and 14 suspected cases. A total of 1629 cases were confirmed, 909 cases recovered and were discharged and no deaths [among this group] were reported.

As of 24:00 on [24 Apr 2020], according to reports from 31 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, there are currently 838 confirmed cases (including 49 severe cases), 77 346 cases were discharged, and 4632 deaths were recorded. A total of 82 816 confirmed cases were reported, and 17 suspected cases are currently [being monitored]. A total of 729 287 close contacts have been traced and 8493 close contacts were still under medical observation.

There were no newly confirmed cases in Hubei, 24 newly recovered cases were discharged (24 in Wuhan), and no new deaths were reported. There are 23 confirmed cases (23 in Wuhan) and no serious cases. A total of 63 593 cases were discharged from hospital (Wuhan 46 441), 4512 deaths were reported (3869 in Wuhan), and 68 128 cases were confirmed (Wuhan 50 333). There are no new suspected cases and no existing suspected cases.

31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities directly under the Central Government) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps reported 29 new cases of asymptomatic infection, including 4 cases of asymptomatic infection imported from abroad; 1 case was confirmed (1 case imported from abroad); 24 cases under observation were discharged (10 cases imported from abroad); 983 cases of asymptomatic infection (150 cases imported from abroad) are still under medical observation.

A total of 1508 confirmed cases were reported from Hong Kong, Macao, and Taiwan: 1035 cases in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (725 cases discharged and 4 deaths), 45 cases in the Macau Special Administrative Region (27 cases discharged), and 428 cases in Taiwan (264 cases discharged and 6 deaths).

