From the English language outbreak report page of 24 Apr 2020 https://www.cdc.go.kr/board/board.es?mid=&bid=0030
KCDC released interim analysis of epidemiological investigation on cases linked to Uijeongbu St Mary's Hospital in Gyeonggi Province.
- From [30 Mar 2020] to [21 Apr 2020], 57 cases within the hospital (patients = 26; nurses = 3; physicians = 2; janitors = 2; caregivers = 10; family/guardians = 14) and 15 cases from local transmission to communities (family = 6; Hantan River Spa Hotel = 7; Asan Medical Center = 2) were confirmed.
- According to the epidemiological investigation, there was a patient who started showing symptoms before symptom onset (26 Mar 2020) of the index case of this cluster. Also, one person who had been discharged from inpatient care at this hospital was confirmed on [20 Mar 2020]. Therefore, it is presumed that transmission occurred in the hospital before [20 Mar 2020]. The infection source has not been identified.
- Some confirmed cases are not from the 8th floor where the index case was receiving inpatient care. Therefore, it is presumed that transmission between different floors occurred by the movement of healthcare workers, caregivers, and/or patients.
- Once the cluster outbreak was identified, central and local governments worked together for response. 58 additional cases were found through their efforts at tracking discharged patients, family/guardians, and caregivers no longer working at the hospital and contact monitoring.
- By testing all contacts, 22 (30.6%) asymptomatic infected persons were identified early. No secondary transmission from asymptomatic case occurred.

