[In the past 24 hours, the tally of confirmed cases of COVID-19 in South Korea has increased by 10 cases and 0 deaths compared with yesterday's 24-hour period (23-24 Apr 2020) when there were 6 newly confirmed cases and no deaths. A total of 10 718 confirmed cases and no new deaths were reported today (24 Apr 2020), up from 10 708 cases and 240 deaths yesterday (23 Apr 2020). The daily newly confirmed case count has been at or below 100 for 23 consecutive days and below 50 for 16 consecutive days. 14 regions did not report any newly confirmed cases and 1 region, Daegu, reported 3 new cases in the past 24 hours. There were 4 newly confirmed cases in quarantine. 4 of the 10 newly confirmed cases were imported cases and 6 were locally transmitted (3 in Daegu and 2 in Gyeonggi and 1 in Seoul.)

From the English language update page (see above) there was a cluster associated with a hospital, involving 57 cases in the hospital (patients and staff and family members/caregivers) and an additional 15 cases in the community. The introduction case has not been identified as yet.

A map of South Korea showing provinces can be seen at https://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/korea-south-administrative-map.htm and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7265865,195. - Mod.MPP]

