[In the 24 hours from 23 to 24 Apr 2020, the total number of cases of COVID-19 confirmed in Iran grew from 87 026 to 88 194, an increase of 1168 newly confirmed cases. The number of deaths has also increased from 5481 to 5574, an increase of 93 deaths in the 24-hour period (as of 24 Apr 2020). In terms of total numbers of confirmed cases, Iran now ranks 8th globally, behind the USA, Spain, Italy, France, Germany, UK, and Turkey, having surpassed China. As with other countries that are lifting business closures, all eyes are on Iran now that "low risk" businesses are opening.

