[The above are the latest breakdowns of confirmed cases of SARS-CoV-2 infection in the USA, as per Worldometer data. The total number of confirmed cases in the USA and territories is now 925 038 including 52 185 deaths, an increase from 880 204 cases and 49 845 deaths in the past 24 hours. New York state, with 277 445 (30.0%) cumulative case reports and 8864 (19.8%) newly confirmed cases over the past 24 hours, is clearly the epicenter of the outbreak in the USA, although case reporting elsewhere is increasing. New York City had a cumulative total of 146 139 as of 2:30 PM on 24 Apr 2020, including 10 746 confirmed deaths and an additional 5102 probable deaths (https://www1.nyc.gov/site/doh/covid/covid-19-data.page).

Daily reported case counts are high in Massachusetts (4946 -- 11.0% of total), Pennsylvania (3096 -- 6.9%), Illinois (2724 -- 6.1%), New Jersey (2171 -- 4.8%), and California (1524 --3.4%). In terms of cumulative case reports, New York is number one, followed by New Jersey, Massachusetts, California, Pennsylvania, Illinois, Michigan, Florida, Louisiana, and Connecticut.

The US Military has confirmed 6213 cumulative cases, with 312 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours. The Veteran Affairs just reported today at 6528 cases. There have been 977 cases reported from federal prisons (unchanged in the past 24 hours) and 1360 cases reported from the Navajo Nation (an increase of 39 in the past 24 hours). Puerto Rico has reported 1276 cases (a decrease of 140 cases in the past 24 hours). I was unable to open the Puerto Rico Health Department website http://salud.gov.pr/ to validate the numbers and the CDC had figures from 23 Apr 2020.

The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention website (https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/cases-updates/cases-in-us.html has a growth curve and a table giving demographics (age and ethnicity) where known.

A map of the United States can be seen at http://www.mapsofworld.com/usa/ and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7265865,106. - Mod.MPP]

